{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two Comment Contexts in JSX"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX mixes two syntactic contexts \u2014 JavaScript and JSX \u2014 and each requires a different comment syntax. Knowing which context you are in determines whether to use JavaScript comment syntax or the JSX comment form."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Diagram showing JSX comment syntax {/* */} inside the JSX tree vs normal JS // and /* */ comments outside JSX",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JavaScript Context: Normal JS Comments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Any code outside the JSX expression tree is plain JavaScript. Here you use the standard JavaScript comment forms:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// This is a JavaScript comment \u2014 before the return\nfunction ProductCard({ name, price, isOnSale }) {\n  // Compute the display price before returning JSX\n  /* Block comment describing the discount logic */\n  const displayPrice = isOnSale ? price * 0.8 : price;\n\n  // You can also comment out entire JSX expressions here\n  // const badge = <SaleBadge />;\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"card\">\n      {/* This is a JSX comment inside the element tree */}\n      <h2>{name}</h2>\n      <p>${displayPrice.toFixed(2)}</p>\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "/* */"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " syntax works anywhere that is valid JavaScript \u2014 function bodies, object literals, before the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "return"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " statement, etc."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX Context: {/* */} Comment Form"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inside the JSX element tree (between opening and closing tags), plain JavaScript comment syntax does not work. JSX is not JavaScript here \u2014 it is JSX syntax that the compiler processes. To include a comment inside the JSX tree, use the block comment inside a JavaScript expression:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Layout({ children }) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"layout\">\n      {/* Navigation section */}\n      <nav>\n        <Logo />\n        <NavLinks />\n      </nav>\n\n      {/*\n        Main content area.\n        Accepts any children \u2014 typically a page component.\n        The children prop is rendered directly here.\n      */}\n      <main>{children}</main>\n\n      {/* Footer is always rendered */}\n      <footer>\n        <FooterLinks />\n      </footer>\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* ... */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " form wraps a JavaScript block comment inside a JSX expression. It produces no output \u2014 no text node, no DOM node, nothing. The compiler simply discards it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistake: // Inside JSX Tree"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trying to use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside the JSX tree either causes a syntax error or renders the comment text literally in the DOM:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// BUG: // in JSX text content \u2192 literal text rendered!\nfunction Header() {\n  return (\n    <h1>\n      // This is NOT a comment \u2014 it renders as text\n      My App\n    </h1>\n  );\n  // Renders: \"// This is NOT a comment \u2014 it renders as text My App\"\n}\n\n// BUG: // at end of JSX line breaks the closing tag\nfunction Header() {\n  return (\n    <div\n      className=\"header\" // This will cause a compile error\n    >\n      My App\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// CORRECT: use {/* */} inside JSX tree\nfunction Header() {\n  return (\n    <h1>\n      {/* Title for the application header */}\n      My App\n    </h1>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Inside JSX: only "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "{/* ... */}"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " is a comment. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "//"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " becomes literal text, "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "<!-- -->"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " HTML comments do not exist in JSX."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTML Comments Do Not Work in JSX"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX does not support HTML comment syntax. Writing "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<!-- ... -->"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside JSX causes a compile error or renders literally:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// BUG: HTML comments are not valid JSX\nfunction Header() {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <!-- This is invalid JSX -->   // syntax error\n      <h1>Title</h1>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// HTML comments in dangerouslySetInnerHTML DO work\n// (they're in raw HTML, not JSX):\nfunction RawHTML({ html }) {\n  return (\n    <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: '<!-- comment --><p>text</p>' }} />\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Commenting Out JSX"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To temporarily disable a block of JSX during development, wrap it in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Sidebar() {\n  return (\n    <aside>\n      <SearchBox />\n\n      {/* Temporarily disabled \u2014 will re-enable when backend is ready\n      <FilterPanel\n        categories={categories}\n        onFilter={handleFilter}\n      />\n      */}\n\n      <RecentItems />\n    </aside>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Alternatively, comment out at the JavaScript level by assigning "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "null"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to a variable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Dashboard() {\n  // Temporarily disabled\n  // const analyticsPanel = <AnalyticsPanel data={data} />;\n  const analyticsPanel = null;\n\n  return (\n    <main>\n      <Overview />\n      {analyticsPanel}\n    </main>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inline Comments on JSX Attributes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You cannot put a comment on the same line as a JSX attribute \u2014 the JSX parser does not allow "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside an opening tag. Use the attribute on its own line and add a comment before it:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// BUG: // inside an opening tag causes a parse error\n<Button\n  className=\"submit\"  // This breaks the JSX\n  onClick={handleClick}\n/>\n\n// CORRECT: comment above the attribute line\n<Button\n  {/* The submit button triggers form validation */}\n  className=\"submit\"\n  onClick={handleClick}\n/>\n\n// Also correct: comment between tags in a separate line\n// Or just use the attribute without inline comments\n<Button\n  className=\"submit\"\n  onClick={handleClick}\n/>{/* End of submit button */}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In practice, most codebases avoid inline JSX attribute comments entirely \u2014 the attribute names and values are usually self-explanatory. Use comments to explain "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "why"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", not "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "what"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript JSDoc in Component Files"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript users often add JSDoc above component definitions and type declarations. This is outside the JSX tree, so standard JavaScript comment syntax applies:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/**\n * Primary action button with loading and disabled states.\n * Renders a <button> element with accessible attributes.\n */\nfunction Button({\n  children,\n  isLoading = false,\n  isDisabled = false,\n  onClick,\n  variant = 'primary',\n}) {\n  return (\n    <button\n      type=\"button\"\n      disabled={isDisabled || isLoading}\n      onClick={onClick}\n      className={`btn btn-${variant}`}\n      aria-busy={isLoading}\n    >\n      {isLoading\n        ? /* Show spinner while loading */ <Spinner size=\"sm\" />\n        : children\n      }\n    </button>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comments and Minification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Build tools (Babel, SWC, Terser) strip all comments from production bundles by default. Neither JavaScript comments nor JSX "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " comments appear in the deployed code. This means:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Comments never increase bundle size in production."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "You can use comments freely in development without worrying about shipping them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "License headers and legal notices may need special configuration to be preserved (Terser's format.comments option)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// In development source:\nfunction App() {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {/* This comment exists only in dev */}\n      <Content />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// In production bundle (minified):\nfunction App(){return React.createElement(\"div\",null,React.createElement(Content,null))}\n// Comment is gone"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Linting Comments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ESLint rules for JSX comments vary by plugin. A few common scenarios:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {
                  "colspan": 1,
                  "rowspan": 1,
                  "colwidth": null
                },
                "content": [
