      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/* eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any */\nfunction wrapAny(value: any) {\n  return <div>{value}</div>;\n}\n\n// Disable a rule for an entire file:\n/* eslint-disable react/display-name */\nexport default () => <div>inline component</div>;\n/* eslint-enable react/display-name */"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JSX has exactly one comment syntax for use inside the element tree: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* block comment */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". This syntax is a JavaScript block comment wrapped in a JSX expression \u2014 it is valid as a child or between attributes. Outside the JSX tree, in the JavaScript portions of the component function, standard "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "/* */"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " comments work as expected. Using "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside JSX text content renders the double-slash as literal characters in the DOM \u2014 a common mistake. HTML "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<!-- -->"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " comments are not valid JSX syntax. All comments are stripped by build tools in production and do not affect bundle size."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Accessibility Annotations in JSX Comments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comments are a useful place to document accessibility decisions \u2014 why a particular ARIA attribute was chosen, why an element is hidden from screen readers, or why a certain tab order was set. These are the \"why\" comments that survive the code's natural evolution:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Modal({ isOpen, title, onClose, children }) {\n  return (\n    <div\n      role=\"dialog\"\n      aria-modal=\"true\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"modal-title\"\n      {/*\n        tabIndex=\"-1\" allows the modal container to receive focus\n        programmatically when opened, so screen readers announce\n        the dialog when keyboard focus moves into it\n      */}\n      tabIndex={-1}\n    >\n      {/* Hidden close button \u2014 accessible but visually icon-only */}\n      <button\n        onClick={onClose}\n        aria-label=\"Close dialog\"\n        className=\"icon-btn\"\n      >\n        {/* aria-hidden hides the icon from AT; aria-label covers the semantics */}\n        <CloseIcon aria-hidden=\"true\" />\n      </button>\n      <h2 id=\"modal-title\">{title}</h2>\n      <div>{children}</div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comments in JSX Expressions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inside a JSX expression "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the content is JavaScript. All JavaScript comment forms are valid:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function PriceDisplay({ price, discount }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <span>\n        {\n          // Apply percentage discount to base price\n          discount\n            ? /* discounted */ (price * (1 - discount)).toFixed(2)\n            : /* full price */ price.toFixed(2)\n        }\n      </span>\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " comment inside "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a JavaScript single-line comment \u2014 it works because the parser is in JavaScript mode inside the curly braces. Only text that is literally in the JSX text content (not inside "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") is a problem for "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "//"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Debugging with Comments: Isolating Renders"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A common development technique is to comment out sections of JSX to bisect a rendering bug. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " form makes this easy without restructuring the component:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function ComplexLayout() {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"app\">\n      <Sidebar />\n\n      {/* DEBUGGING: commenting out to isolate CSS conflict */}\n      {/*\n      <Header />\n      */}\n\n      <main>\n        {/* Temporarily render plain text to check data flow */}\n        {/* <ArticleList articles={articles} /> */}\n        <pre>{JSON.stringify(articles, null, 2)}</pre>\n      </main>\n\n      <Footer />\n    </div>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After debugging, restoring the commented code is trivial. Many developers also use code editor features like \"toggle block comment\" (Ctrl+/) with the cursor inside JSX \u2014 their editor should automatically use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{/* */}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " when in JSX context (VS Code, WebStorm, and Neovim with the right plugin all support this)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript: @ts-ignore and @ts-expect-error in JSX Files"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript directives are JavaScript comments, so they work above JSX expressions the same way they work in plain TypeScript:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function LegacyWrapper({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      {/*\n        @ts-ignore \u2014 OldLibraryComponent has incomplete type definitions\n        in v1.x. Remove when we upgrade to v2 (tracked in issue #456).\n      */}\n      {/* @ts-ignore */}\n      <OldLibraryComponent />\n      {children}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// @ts-expect-error (preferred over @ts-ignore since TS 3.9):\n// expects an error on the next line \u2014 fails the build if no error occurs\n{/* @ts-expect-error \u2014 temporarily passing null while API is fixed */}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Prefer "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "@ts-expect-error"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " over "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "@ts-ignore"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " in new code \u2014 if the expected error is ever fixed, "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "@ts-expect-error"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " causes a "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "new"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " TypeScript error telling you the suppression is now redundant. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "@ts-ignore"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " is silent even when the underlying error is gone."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comment Best Practices for JSX Components"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The same principles that apply to code comments in general apply to JSX components, with a few JSX-specific additions:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Explain the why, not the what. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "JSX is often self-documenting. Comment unusual decisions, workarounds for browser bugs, or non-obvious prop combinations."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Use JSDoc above the component for tooling. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "/** */ above the function gives editors type hints and hover documentation for the component."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Avoid noise comments. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{/* render button */} before a <button> adds nothing. The JSX itself says that."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Comment disabled code with a TODO. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "If you comment out JSX temporarily, add a TODO with a ticket number so it doesn't get forgotten."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Use {/* */} consistently for JSX regions. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Consistent style helps editors and grep find comments reliably."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "jsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Good JSX comments:\n\n// 1. Explain non-obvious attributes\n<video\n  muted          {/* Required by Chrome autoplay policy \u2014 see crbug.com/776546 */}\n  playsInline    {/* Prevents fullscreen on iOS Safari */}\n  autoPlay\n  src={src}\n/>\n\n// 2. Document conditional logic\n{/*\n  Only show premium badge if user.plan === 'pro' OR 'enterprise'.\n  The 'trial' plan gets the same UI as free but with a countdown.\n  See docs/billing-tiers.md for the full matrix.\n*/}\n{(user.plan === 'pro' || user.plan === 'enterprise') && <PremiumBadge />}\n\n// 3. TODO with context\n{/* TODO(#1234): Replace with <NewAuthFlow /> once feature flag is removed */}\n{/* <NewAuthFlow /> */}\n<LegacyAuthFlow />"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Key takeaways: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inside JSX tree: {/* ... */} only. Outside JSX (in JS): // and /* */ as normal. // inside JSX text \u2192 literal text rendered in DOM (bug). HTML <!-- --> comments don't exist in JSX. All comments are stripped in production builds. Use JSDoc above components for editor tooling and type documentation."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}